-- Romanian Leu Gains 3rd Day, Tops Eastern Europe And Africa Peers
-- B y   A n d r a   T i m u   a n d   I r i n a   S a v u
-- 2013-04-16T10:45:35Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-04-16/romanian-leu-gains-3rd-day-tops-eastern-europe-and-africa-peers.html
The leu strengthened for a third
day, heading for its highest level in a month.  The leu appreciated less than 0.1 percent to 4.3760 per
euro by 1:37 p.m. in Bucharest, the highest level on a closing
basis since March 11, according to data compiled by Bloomberg.  The currency has added 1.7 percent this year, the best
performer among eastern European and African currencies tracked
by Bloomberg.  To contact the reporters on this story:
